The paper presents a dynamic algorithm for the recognition of proper circular-arc graphs, which involves data structures and graph algorithms. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the minimally non-PHCA and non-PIG induced subgraphs, which are related to graph theory and combinatorics, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions constant-time operations, which could indicate that it belongs to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
